cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.MM. 

This paper focuses on semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task, and proposes a novel approach based on attention mechanisms. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves optimization of features, which is related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, hence cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely. The use of attention mechanisms is a popular topic in deep learning and neural networks, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on two popular datasets in computer vision, Cityscapes and PASCAL VOC 2012, which is related to multimedia and multimodal processing, hence cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible sub-category.
